Description: Body sherd of Aeolian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; interior glazed black; exterior: from top, part of guilloche frieze; painted decoration consisting of confronted goats (head, horn shoulder and part of foreleg remaining of first goat; part of horn of second); pendant triangle and elaborate cross as filling ornament; inscription on exterior.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group (?)
Curator's comments: '110' in pencil on inside; label 'A 785' on outside. Probably from same vase as 1924,1201.1028 and 1965,0930.710; possibly from the same vase as Boston MFA 88.949.
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 252, no. 396)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.05)
